Durlag traveled with a number of adventurers, people he could call close companions. Included among these brave souls were [[Arlo Stoneblade]], [[Grael]], [[Hengriffe]], [[Chalmon]], [[Tuorna Brightarm]], and even the [[dragon]] [[Mechezarin]].{{fact}}

Durlag was the son of [[Bolhur the Clanless|Bolhur "Thunderaxe" the Clanless]], the great dwarven hero who was never able to start his own clan.

Durlag's family were quite powerful and daring in their own right. His wife [[Islanne]] was a powerful magic-wielder who was tragically killed by a [[doppelganger]] who took Durlag's form. He had two known sons, [[Kiel|Kiel "The Legion Killer"]], and [[Fuernebol]], the young dwarf who was more skilled with a bow than a sword or axe.
